This directory contains the full run setup used for the FLAMINGO simulations.
The simulations are introduced in Schaye et al. (2023) with the strategy for
calibration of the free parameters introduced in Kugel et al. (2023).

More information about the FLAMINGO project can be found on the project's
webpage: https://flamingo.strw.leidenuniv.nl/

For standard runs, the code should be configured with:

--with-subgrid=FLAMINGO --with-hydro=sphenix --with-kernel=wendland-C2 --enable-lightcone

OR for the models with collimated jet feedback:

--with-subgrid=SPIN_JET_FLAMINGO --with-hydro=sphenix --with-kernel=wendland-C2 --enable-lightcone

(and any other optimization, library or compiler parameters specific
to your system. Note that the lightcone module requires the Healpix library.)

The scripts in the L1_m9 directory download the tables equired to run the
fiducial FLAMINGO model. The ICs are a (100 Mpc)^3 volume at the same resolution
as the large FLAMINGO runs but in a volume 1000x smaller.  Information about how
to generate the exact ICs used in the official FLAMINGO simulations can be found
on the project webpage (see above).

Note that the example runs with the particle-lightcone and a set of healpix
shells switched on. In a 100 Mpc volume, this will lead to a large number of
replications and is thus not advised. We nevertheless include the parameters
here for completeness.

The feedback parameters in the L1_m9/flamingo.yml parameter file are the
parameters running the L1_m9 model of Schaye et al. (2023).

The feedback parameters in the L1_m9/flamingo_jet.yml parameter file are the
parameters running the Jet model of Schaye et al. (2023).

To run the feedback variations, the following parameters have to be changed
in L1_m9/flamingo.yml (Table 8 of Kugel et al. 2023):

Parameter                              | fgas+2σ | L1_m9   | fgas-2σ | fgas-4σ | fgas-8σ |  M*-σ   | M*-σ+fgas-4σ |
---------------------------------------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+--------------+
EAGLEFeedback:SNII_energy_fraction_min | 0.219   | 0.238   | 0.206   | 0.191   | 0.145   | 0.322   |      0.261   |
EAGLEFeedback:SNII_energy_fraction_max | 0.219   | 0.238   | 0.206   | 0.191   | 0.145   | 0.322   |      0.261   |
EAGLEFeedback:SNII_delta_v_km_p_s      |   577   |   562   |   552   |   532   |   483   |   608   |        557   |
EAGLEAGN:AGN_delta_T_K                 | 5.143e7 | 8.801e7 | 1.202e8 | 1.619e8 | 2.514e8 | 1.135e8 |      1.888e8 |
EAGLEAGN:boost_beta                    | 0.554   | 0.514   | 0.497   | 0.482   | 0.462   | 0.626   |      0.620   |
---------------------------------------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+---------+--------------+

For jet models, the following parameters have to be changed in L1_m9/flamingo_jet.yml
(Table 8 of Kugel et al. 2023):

Parameter                              |  Jet     | Jet+fgas-4σ |
---------------------------------------+----------+-------------+
EAGLEFeedback:SNII_energy_fraction_min |  0.166   |     0.176   |
EAGLEFeedback:SNII_energy_fraction_max |  0.166   |     0.176   |
EAGLEFeedback:SNII_delta_v_km_p_s      |    477   |       527   |
SPINJETAGN:v_jet_km_p_s                |    836   |      1995   |
SPINJETAGN:boost_beta                  |  0.597   |     0.482   |
---------------------------------------+----------+-------------+




